SELECT 
        'Training' as dataset,
        product_category,
        COUNT(*) as records,
        MIN(date) as start_date,
        MAX(date) as end_date
     FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.training_data`
     GROUP BY product_category
     UNION ALL
     SELECT 
        'Test' as dataset,
        product_category,
        COUNT(*) as records,
        MIN(date) as start_date,
        MAX(date) as end_date
     FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.test_data`
     GROUP BY product_category
     ORDER BY dataset, product_category

SELECT 
        product_category,
        COUNT(*) as record_count,
        ROUND(AVG(sales_ma7), 2) as avg_7day_ma,
        ROUND(AVG(sales_ma30), 2) as avg_30day_ma,
        COUNT(CASE WHEN is_holiday_season = 1 THEN 1 END) as holiday_records
     FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.features_timeseries`
     GROUP BY product_category
     ORDER BY product_category

SELECT 
        product_category,
        COUNT(*) as total_records,
        COUNT(DISTINCT date) as unique_dates,
        MIN(date) as start_date,
        MAX(date) as end_date,
        DATE_DIFF(MAX(date), MIN(date), DAY) + 1 as expected_days
     FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.unified_sales`
     GROUP BY product_category
     ORDER BY product_category

SELECT 
        product_category,
        COUNT(*) as prediction_count,
        ROUND(AVG(predicted_sales), 2) as avg_predicted_sales,
        ROUND(MIN(predicted_sales), 2) as min_predicted_sales,
        ROUND(MAX(predicted_sales), 2) as max_predicted_sales,
        MIN(forecast_date) as first_forecast_date,
        MAX(forecast_date) as last_forecast_date
     FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.all_predictions`
     GROUP BY product_category
     ORDER BY product_category

SELECT 
        model_name,
        model_type,
        product_category,
        version,
        status,
        FORMAT_TIMESTAMP('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', training_date) as training_date
     FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.model_registry`
     ORDER BY product_category

SELECT 
        table_id as table_name,
        type as table_type,
        TIMESTAMP_MILLIS(creation_time) as created_at,
        row_count
     FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.__TABLES__`
     ORDER BY table_id
SELECT * FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.data_lineage`
SELECT * FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.model_registry`

WITH table_info AS (
  SELECT 
    'raw_electronics_sales' as table_name,
    COUNT(*) as row_count
  FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.raw_electronics_sales`
  
  UNION ALL
  
  SELECT 
    'raw_apparel_sales' as table_name,
    COUNT(*) as row_count
  FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.raw_apparel_sales`
  
  UNION ALL
  
  SELECT 
    'raw_home_garden_sales' as table_name,
    COUNT(*) as row_count
  FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.raw_home_garden_sales`
  
  UNION ALL
  
  SELECT 
    'unified_sales' as table_name,
    COUNT(*) as row_count
  FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.unified_sales`
  
  UNION ALL
  
  SELECT 
    'features_timeseries' as table_name,
    COUNT(*) as row_count
  FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.features_timeseries`
  
  UNION ALL
  
  SELECT 
    'training_data' as table_name,
    COUNT(*) as row_count
  FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.training_data`
  
  UNION ALL
  
  SELECT 
    'test_data' as table_name,
    COUNT(*) as row_count
  FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.test_data`
  
  UNION ALL
  
  SELECT 
    'all_predictions' as table_name,
    COUNT(*) as row_count
  FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.all_predictions`
)
SELECT 
  table_name,
  row_count,
  ROUND(row_count * 0.0001, 4) as estimated_size_gb,
  ROUND(row_count * 0.0001 * 0.02, 6) as monthly_storage_cost_usd,
  ROUND(row_count * 0.0001 * 0.02 * 12, 4) as annual_storage_cost_usd
FROM table_info
ORDER BY row_count DESC;

-- QUERY 30: Alert for Prediction Drift
CREATE OR REPLACE TABLE `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.prediction_alerts` AS
SELECT 
  product_category,
  forecast_date,
  predicted_sales,
  CASE 
    WHEN predicted_sales > (SELECT AVG(predicted_sales) * 2 
                           FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.all_predictions` 
                           WHERE product_category = p.product_category)
    THEN 'HIGH_PREDICTION_ALERT'
    WHEN predicted_sales < (SELECT AVG(predicted_sales) * 0.3 
                           FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.all_predictions` 
                           WHERE product_category = p.product_category)
    THEN 'LOW_PREDICTION_ALERT'
    ELSE 'NORMAL'
  END as alert_status,
  CURRENT_TIMESTAMP() as alert_timestamp
FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.all_predictions` p
WHERE 
  predicted_sales > (SELECT AVG(predicted_sales) * 2 FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.all_predictions` WHERE product_category = p.product_category)
  OR predicted_sales < (SELECT AVG(predicted_sales) * 0.3 FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.all_predictions` WHERE product_category = p.product_category);

-- QUERY 28: Data Quality Monitoring
CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.data_quality_monitor` AS
WITH category_stats AS (
  SELECT 
    product_category,
    AVG(sales_quantity) as avg_sales_category,
    STDDEV(sales_quantity) as stddev_sales_category
  FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.unified_sales`
  GROUP BY product_category
)
SELECT 
  u.product_category,
  DATE_TRUNC(u.date, WEEK) as week,
  COUNT(*) as record_count,
  COUNT(DISTINCT u.date) as unique_dates,
  ROUND(AVG(u.sales_quantity), 2) as avg_sales,
  ROUND(STDDEV(u.sales_quantity), 2) as stddev_sales,
  -- Detect anomalies (> 3 standard deviations)
  COUNTIF(ABS(u.sales_quantity - s.avg_sales_category) > 3 * s.stddev_sales_category) as anomaly_count
FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.unified_sales` u
JOIN category_stats s ON u.product_category = s.product_category
GROUP BY u.product_category, week
ORDER BY u.product_category, week DESC
LIMIT 100;

-- QUERY 28: Data Quality Monitoring
CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.data_quality_monitor` AS
SELECT 
  product_category,
  DATE_TRUNC(date, WEEK) as week,
  COUNT(*) as record_count,
  COUNT(DISTINCT date) as unique_dates,
  ROUND(AVG(sales_quantity), 2) as avg_sales,
  ROUND(STDDEV(sales_quantity), 2) as stddev_sales,
  -- Detect anomalies (> 3 standard deviations)
  COUNTIF(ABS(sales_quantity - AVG(sales_quantity) OVER (PARTITION BY product_category)) 
          > 3 * STDDEV(sales_quantity) OVER (PARTITION BY product_category)) as anomaly_count
FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.unified_sales`
GROUP BY product_category, week
ORDER BY product_category, week DESC
LIMIT 100;

SELECT 
  DATE_TRUNC(date, MONTH) as month_start,
  product_category,
  SUM(sales_quantity) as total_sales,
  AVG(sales_quantity) as avg_daily_sales,
  SUM(revenue) as total_revenue,
  AVG(revenue) as avg_daily_revenue,
  STDDEV(sales_quantity) as sales_stddev,
  MIN(sales_quantity) as min_sales,

-- QUERY 5: Verify Feature Store
SELECT 
  product_category,
  COUNT(*) as record_count,
  MIN(date) as start_date,
  MAX(date) as end_date,
  ROUND(AVG(sales_ma7), 2) as avg_7day_ma,
  ROUND(AVG(sales_ma30), 2) as avg_30day_ma
FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.features_timeseries`
GROUP BY product_category
ORDER BY product_category;

-- QUERY 4: Create Feature Store - Time-based Features
CREATE OR REPLACE TABLE `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.features_timeseries` AS
SELECT 
  date,
  product_category,
  sales_quantity,
  revenue,
  
  -- Moving averages
  AVG(sales_quantity) OVER (
    PARTITION BY product_category 
    ORDER BY date 
    ROWS BETWEEN 6 PRECEDING AND CURRENT ROW
  ) as sales_ma7,
  
  AVG(sales_quantity) OVER (
    PARTITION BY product_category 
    ORDER BY date 
    ROWS BETWEEN 29 PRECEDING AND CURRENT ROW
  ) as sales_ma30,
  
  AVG(revenue) OVER (
    PARTITION BY product_category 
    ORDER BY date 
    ROWS BETWEEN 6 PRECEDING AND CURRENT ROW
  ) as revenue_ma7,
  
  -- Lag features
  LAG(sales_quantity, 1) OVER (PARTITION BY product_category ORDER BY date) as sales_lag1,
  LAG(sales_quantity, 7) OVER (PARTITION BY product_category ORDER BY date) as sales_lag7,
  LAG(sales_quantity, 30) OVER (PARTITION BY product_category ORDER BY date) as sales_lag30,
  
  -- Year-over-year comparison
  LAG(sales_quantity, 365) OVER (PARTITION BY product_category ORDER BY date) as sales_yoy,
  
  -- Seasonality indicators
  EXTRACT(DAYOFWEEK FROM date) as day_of_week_num,
  EXTRACT(MONTH FROM date) as month_num,
  EXTRACT(QUARTER FROM date) as quarter,
  EXTRACT(DAYOFYEAR FROM date) as day_of_year,
  
  -- Holiday indicators
  CASE 
    WHEN EXTRACT(MONTH FROM date) = 12 AND EXTRACT(DAY FROM date) BETWEEN 20 AND 31 THEN 1
    WHEN EXTRACT(MONTH FROM date) = 11 AND EXTRACT(DAY FROM date) BETWEEN 20 AND 30 THEN 1
    ELSE 0
  END as is_holiday_season,
  
  CURRENT_TIMESTAMP() as feature_timestamp
  
FROM `playground-s-11-8124ae0d.retail_ml.unified_sales`
ORDER BY product_category, date;
